{
  "formatVersion": 6,
  "nxslVersionV5": true,
  "description": "Microsoft SQL Server monitoring via the nxagentd mssql subagent. Uses agent-list instance discovery to enumerate configured server connections (MSSQL.Connections) and all databases across them (MSSQL.AllDatabases), creating per-server and per-database vital DCIs. Counter metrics use average-per-second (throughput) or average-per-minute (rare events) delta calculation.",
  "events": [],
  "templates": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "guid": "6948eb95-d0d2-47e5-8600-0228c4a5479b",
      "name": "MSSQL Server",
      "comments": "Monitors Microsoft SQL Server through the nxagentd 'mssql' subagent. Requires the subagent to be enabled on the node with at least one [mssql/connections/<id>] section (see bundled agent policy). Per-connection DCIs discover from MSSQL.Connections; per-database DCIs discover from MSSQL.AllDatabases, whose rows are emitted as 'connectionId,databaseName' and expand directly into the MSSQL.Database.* (connectionId, database) signature.",
